HEADWORD: ethic
<hw>eth"ic</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧th"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>the principles of right and wrong that are accepted by an
individual or a social group; <as>as, the Puritan
<ex>ethic</ex></as>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> moral principle, value-system, value
orientation.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a system of principles governing morality and
acceptable conduct.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ethical code.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ethically</ent>⟦br⟧
